  <brief_title>Extended-release vs Immediate-release Metformin in PCOS Women</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Catholic University of the Sacred Heart</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Catholic University of the Sacred Heart</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of our study is to compare the different effects of 6 months treatment with
      extended-release metformin and immediate-release metformin on clinical, endocrine and
      metabolic parameters in women affected by polycystic ovary syndrome. We also evaluate
      gastrointestinal disorders associated with the two different compouds.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
